<font color="#FF0000">THE DEMON BELOW</font><br>
<tt>Thu Sep 25 21:16:17 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Spent a lot of time in the dark.  That's when the &quot;Silent Warriors&quot; went to work.  It was a peaceful time in which I exercised the control.  As you say hours and hours of boredom interspersed with moments of stark terror.<br><br>
I found that fear at the base level heightened my awareness.  As soon as I felt anything less I wasn't sharp, I was then on the dark side.  As fear for whatever reason increased a different level would appear.  It would increase until I stripped all social inhibitions and the basic animal was in full bloom.  Blind killing rage.<br><br>
Rage for the enemy is one thing, but for your own was something that has always bothered me.  Once when I had spent days without food and had been pushed to the limit I did something I will always remember.  I was using my last soup mix and heating over the only fire I could muster in the rain.  A tired totally innocent kid kicked over the field cup.  In a blinding rage I launched with a knife in hand and proceeded to kill him.  Only a buddy stopped the inevitable.  I never knew his name, but I will not forget his look of horror.  It still haunts me how stress can strip away all humanity.  Lucky.<br><br>
Not long after I was celebrating several hundred missions and was only drunk.  On a simple bar room challenge I snapped the bottom of a bottle and went for the kill.  Stopped again.  This time I knew I was in trouble.  Humanity was slipping away.<br><br>
I pushed any feeling deeper in the pit.  I knew this was the trigger and something I could not afford.  Some times I knew I was my own target.<br><br>
We are all animals tempered by social inhibitions.  Those inhibitions are what layers all that humanity on top of that the wild animal.<br><br>
The situation stripped away these inhibitions which act as controls.  Our guilt is our demon which haunts us for returning if only briefly to the animal state.  The demon is us without the constraints of civilization.  To glimpse it is to remember.<br>

<p><code>--   (SW) </code><p>


